Legal/Ethical Considerations

The Claude-2 repository explicitly frames itself as security research/educational use only. The maintainer references Hong Minhee's essay "Is legal the same as legitimate: AI reimplementation and the erosion of copyleft" — suggesting awareness that raw legality ≠ ethical legitimacy.

For your Swibe usage:
- ✅ Architecture patterns — Fair game (ideas aren't copyrightable)
- ✅ API designs — Public interface study
- ⚠️ Direct code copying — Avoid; implement Swibe-idiomatically
- ✅ Conceptual inspiration — Tool systems, permission models, MCP integration

The research framing protects defensive analysis but doesn't grant unlimited reuse rights. Treat this as architectural study rather than source material.

